FT  02 NOV 92 / Warning over skills shortages
HIGH LEVELS of skills shortages in the west Midlands may show up rapidly
when the UK pulls out of recession, according to a study published by the
Department of Employment.
Mr Paul Thomas, regional director, said the level of academic and vocational
qualifications of school leavers and workers continued to be below the
national average.
West Midland Labour Market. Employment Department, Alpha Tower, Suffolk
Street, Birmingham B1 1UR.
